SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1121
By Lowe
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Michael J. "Mike" Smith
upon his retirement as Bradley County Trustee.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should honor
those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout their
careers in public service; and
WHEREAS, Michael J. "Mike" Smith is one such estimable individual, who, after many
years of dedicated service to the people of Bradley County, is taking a well-deserved retirement
as Bradley County Trustee; and
WHEREAS, a 1971 graduate of Bradley Central High School, Mr. Smith furthered his
training at the Tennessee Law Enforcement Academy; and
WHEREAS, he began his professional career as a deputy sheriff with the Bradley
County Sheriff's Office in the 1970s, rising to the rank of sergeant, and later continued his
career in the private sector with Mars Candy Company from 1979 until 2004; and
WHEREAS, returning to public service, Mike Smith served as the environmental officer
for the Bradley County Sheriff's Office from 2004 to 2006; and
WHEREAS, he further distinguished himself in elected office, serving as a Bradley
County Commissioner from 1990 to 2006, including service as chairman on multiple occasions
and as chairman of the Finance Committee; and
WHEREAS, in 2006, Mr. Smith was elected Bradley County Trustee, a position in which
he has served with integrity and diligence for nearly two decades, earning the trust and respect
of the citizens he has served; and
WHEREAS, throughout his tenure, he has achieved numerous professional distinctions,
including designation as a Certified Public Administrator through the Tennessee County Officials
Certificate Training Program in 2007, recognition as Trustee of the Year by the East Tennessee
SJR1121
017834
- 1 -

Trustees' Association on multiple occasions, and service as past president of that organization;
and
WHEREAS, Mike Smith was honored as Bradley County Republican Man of the Year in
2017, and he was inducted into the Bradley County Republican Hall of Fame, reflecting the high
regard in which he is held by his peers and community; and
WHEREAS, beyond his many professional accomplishments, Mr. Smith has been
actively involved in the Bradley County and Cleveland community, contributing his time and
talents to various organizations and youth athletics programs, both as a player and as a coach;
and
WHEREAS, Mike Smith is devoted to his family and shares a loving marriage with his
wife, Deborah Smith; and
WHEREAS, throughout his distinguished career, Mr. Smith has demonstrated the utmost
professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the unbridled respect and admiration of his
colleagues and the citizens he has served; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Michael J. "Mike" Smith
upon his retirement as Bradley County Trustee, thank him for his many years of dedicated
service, and extend to him our heartfelt wishes for a happy and fulfilling retirement and every
continued success in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
